All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Action
    Interface for actions produced by the rules at each frame.
    AddNode<T>
    The node model used to add two objects.
    AndNode
    The node model used to perform logical AND.
    CompareNode<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    The node model used to compare two objects.
    CurEntityNode
    The node model used to get the entity being processed.
    CurSpeciesNode
    The node model used to get the species being processed.
    DeathRule
    Rule used to kill entities.
    DimNode
    The node model used to get the game's grid dimensions.
    DoubleAddNode
    The node model used to add two doubles.
    Edge
    This class provides the abstract edge model for the edges used in the nodal system.
    Entity
    Each entity is part of a species.
    EqualNode<T>
    The node model used to test equality between two objects.
    GameManager
    The game manager is responsible for the initialization and evolution of the game state at each frame using the rules defined by the user.
    GenerateAction
    Action used to generate new members in a species.
    GenerateNode
    The node model used as terminal node in a generation rule's network.
    GenerationRule
    Rule used to generate new members in a species.
    IfElseNode<T>
    The node model used to perform IF/ELSE statement.
    Input
    This class provides the abstract model for the input(s) of the nodes in the nodal system.
    IntAddNode
    The node model used to add two integers.
    KillAction
    Action used to kill an entity, meaning removing ot from its species.
    KillNode
    The node model used as terminal node in a death rule's network.
    MoveAction
    Action used to move entities.
    MovementRule
    Rule used to move entities.
    MoveNode
    The node model used as terminal node in a movement rule's network.
    Network
    This class provides the abstract model for the networks with in the nodal system when defining rules for the game.
    Node
    This class provides the abstract node model for the nodes used in the nodal system.
    NotNode
    The node model used to negate a boolean.
    OrNode
    The node model used to perform logical OR.
    Output
    This class provides the abstract model for the output(s) of the nodes in the nodal system.
    RandDoubleNode
    The node model used to generate a random number in the range [0, 1[.
    RandIntNode
    The node model used to generate a random integer in the range [0, N[.
    Rule
    Abstract model for the rules defined by the user through a network of operators.
    Species
    A species represents a group of homogeneous entities, which all behave according to the same rules.
    Surface
    Each instance of this class represents a different kind of surface that can be stored on a tile.
    SurfaceAtNode
    The node model used to get the surface in the tile at a given position.
    Terrain
    A terrain is a 2D grid of tiles, each tile containing a surface.
    TerrainStack
    This class represents the model used to stack terrains on top of each other (like Photoshop layers).
    TimeNode
    The node model used to get the current frame.
    Vec2D
    An instance of the Vec2D class is a 2D vector with integer coordinates.
    VecAddNode
    The node model used to add two 2D vectors.
